We recommend maintaining strict quarantine and control measures until early March in Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou, and Shenzhen, and until late March in Hunan. This model could be valuable in predicting epidemic trends and offering guidance for countries at high risk, such as South Korea, Japan, Italy, and Iran.

The coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19) has spread rapidly in China and to more than 30 other countries in the past two months. It has unique characteristics, including high infectivity during incubation, delays between real dynamics and reported cases, and the impact of quarantine measures. Our SUQC model was developed to track the dynamics of COVID-19 and predict epidemic trends. This model can also offer guidance for other countries facing high outbreak risks, like South Korea, Japan, and Iran. © Higher Education Press and Springer-Verlag GmbH Germany, part of Springer Nature 2020.
